<p>I'm trying to find the maximum number in an array using Divide and Conquer Method(recursion). But when I compile this code, I'm getting ArrayIndexOutOfBounds exception.</p>  <p>I'm not sure where I'm going wrong. Here is my code snippet:</p>  <pre><code>public class ... {   int[] A = {2,4,5,1,6,7,9,3};   int max;    public void solution() {     max = findMax(0, A.length-1);     //print max   }    private int findMax(int a, int b){         if(b-a == 1){         return A[a]&gt;A[b] ? A[a] : A[b];     }     else if(a==b){         return A[a];     }      return findMax(findMax(a, (a+b)/2), findMax((a+b)/2 +1, b));   }  } </code></pre>